# Commit messages

When asked to generate a Git commit message (including Cursor AI Commit), **ALWAYS** output a valid [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/) message.

This repo enforces the format via **Commitlint** (`commitlint.config.js`) on the `commit-msg` Husky hook.

## Output format

```
<type>(optional-scope): <subject>

<body>
```

**Output only the commit message.** No explanations, no markdown fences, no commentary.

## Template (preferred)

```
<type>(optional-scope): <short lowercase summary>

- Bullet point 1
- Bullet point 2
- Bullet point 3
```

## Types (first line MUST start with one of these)

- `feat`
- `fix`
- `chore`
- `docs`
- `refactor`
- `perf`
- `test`
- `build`
- `ci`
- `style`
- `revert`

## Subject rules

- Lowercase (no PascalCase / UPPERCASE)
- Imperative mood (“add”, “fix”, “introduce” — not “added” / “fixes”)
- Must **not** end with a period
- Prefer under **72** characters; hard max **100** (Commitlint `header-max-length`)
- Never use a bare GitHub-style title like `Update README` or `Fix bug` without a type prefix
- Do not start the subject with “Update”, “Refactor”, or “Add” as a substitute for the type — the type comes first: `feat(…): add …`

## Scope (optional)

- **kebab-case** only (Commitlint `scope-case`)
- Prefer package or area names, e.g. `core`, `events`, `ai`, `brand`, `backlog`, `tooling`

## Body rules

- Separate from the subject with **one blank line**
- Wrap every body line at **100** characters or less
- Use `- ` bullet points for multiple changes
- Focus on **why** / notable deltas; keep calm and precise (JobJitsu voice)

## Examples

```
feat(ai): introduce local intelligence provider contracts

- Add AiProvider interface
- Add AiProviderRegistry interface
- Export provider types
- Update README to document the new architecture
- Expand tests for provider contracts
```

```
feat(events): add in-memory event bus

- Implement createInMemoryEventBus with ordered delivery
- Support optional durable sink for egress events
- Cover pub/sub and unsubscribe in unit tests
```

```
docs(brand): align ui copy with agent on-device terminology

- Prefer Agent over LLM in user-facing chrome
- Document branding-for-development rules
```

```
chore(tooling): configure commitlint husky and lint-staged
```
